<blockquote> <p>Competencies: Verbal communication &amp; self development- awareness of strengths and areas for development, pursuing and applying feedback, multi-tasking in a fast-paced environment, maintaining a successful personal brand while providing critical feedback,
        Professionalism - Being present and prepared, prioritizing and completing tasks to accomplish goals.</p> 
        <p>Students choose one shape to and, using the principles and elements of design, they create an interesting composition. They use color theory to add depth, contrast and focal points with acrylic painting. Color choices are a response to the placement of previous hues -mixing one color at a time. Students must decide when an area will be repainted with a different hue as the painting develops. No color studies are made before beginning the final painting, so students are reacting to color and composition on the painted surface.</p></blockquote>

</worksheet>
